  "body": "### What's your issue about?\r\n\r\nIf you set a global at the top of a viper source file (outside of any contract methods), nothing changes and no exception or warning is raised.\r\n\r\n```bash\r\n(viper)$ cat test*.v.py\r\n# test-false.v.py\r\ntest: bool = false\r\n\r\ndef toggle():\r\n    self.test = not self.test\r\n\r\n# test-true.v.py\r\ntest: bool = true\r\n\r\ndef toggle():\r\n    self.test = not self.test\r\n\r\n(viper)$ diff <(./bin/viper test-false.v.py) <(./bin/viper test-true.v.py)\r\n(viper)$ # No difference\r\n```\r\n### How can it be fixed?\r\n\r\nTwo options, either that syntax fails:\r\n```python\r\nimport pytest\r\nfrom pytest import raises\r\nfrom viper import compiler\r\n\r\ndef test_global_setter():\r\n    bad_code = \"\"\"\r\nswitch: public(bool) = false\r\n\r\ndef toggle():\r\n    self.switch = not self.switch\r\n\"\"\"\r\n    with raises(Exception):\r\n        # Fails due to setting global outside of method\r\n        compiler.compile(bad_code)\r\n```\r\n\r\nOr the syntax is allowed and somehow sets the initial state:\r\n```python\r\nimport pytest\r\nfrom .setup_transaction_tests import get_contract\r\n\r\ndef test_block_number():\r\n    notset_code = \"\"\"\r\nswitch: public(bool)\r\n\r\ndef toggle():\r\n    self.switch = not self.switch\r\n\"\"\"\r\n    false_code = \"\"\"\r\nswitch: public(bool) = false\r\n\r\ndef toggle():\r\n    self.switch = not self.switch\r\n\"\"\"\r\n\r\n    true_code = \"\"\"\r\nswitch: public(bool) = true\r\n\r\ndef toggle():\r\n    self.switch = not self.switch\r\n\"\"\"\r\n    # All three compile\r\n    cn = get_contract(notset_code)\r\n    cf = get_contract(false_code)\r\n    ct = get_contract(true_code)\r\n\r\n    # Toggling works\r\n    assert cn.get_switch() == cf.get_switch()\r\n    cn.toggle()\r\n    assert cn.get_switch() != cf.get_switch()\r\n    cf.toggle()\r\n    assert cn.get_switch() and cf.get_switch()\r\n    assert cn.get_switch() == cf.get_switch()\r\n\r\n    # cf.switch is true at this point\r\n    # This doesn't work as expected (fails)\r\n    assert ct.get_switch() == cf.get_switch()\r\n    ct.toggle()\r\n    # But this works\r\n    assert ct.get_switch() == cf.get_switch()\r\n```\r\n\r\n#### Cute Animal Picture\r\n\r\n![aardvark](https://assets3.thrillist.com/v1/image/2509330/size/tmg-article_tall;jpeg_quality=20.jpg)\r\n",
